				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="太陽と月の王国 (Taiyo to Tsuki no Oukoku)" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>&amp;#229;&amp;#164;&amp;#170;&amp;#233;&amp;#153;&amp;#189;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#168;&amp;#230;&amp;#156;&amp;#136;&amp;#227;&amp;#129;&amp;#174;&amp;#231;&amp;#142;&amp;#139;&amp;#229;&amp;#155;&amp;#189; (Taiyo to Tsuki no Oukoku), roughly translated as Kingdom of the Sun and the Moon, is a climbing game where there will be one loser among the players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game uses a pyramid deck of cards (one 1, two 2s,..., ten 10s) and a player's &amp;quot;hand&amp;quot; of cards is split between cards that are dealt to a traditional hand, and cards that form a pyramid in front of each player.  This pyramid is face down, except for the front row, and players can choose to play cards from their hand, their pyramid, or a combination.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players can play the same rank as a previous player, and if 4 of the same rank have been played, the round ends immediately, with the current player winning that round and the ranks of cards reversing.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Rounds continue until only 1 player has cards left in hand; that player loses 1 life.  Once 1 player has lost both of their lives, the game ends, and they lose.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
